  1→# Data Models — mcp-server-auth
  2→
  3→## Schema Changes
  4→
  5→### `mcp_server` — New Fields
  6→
  7→```sql
  8→-- Auth mode: determines how Brain authenticates with this server
  9→DEFINE FIELD OVERWRITE auth_mode ON mcp_server TYPE string
 10→  DEFAULT "none"
 11→  ASSERT $value IN ["none", "static_headers", "oauth", "provider"];
 12→
 13→-- Static headers: array of { name, value_encrypted } pairs
 14→-- Only populated when auth_mode = "static_headers"
 15→DEFINE FIELD OVERWRITE static_headers ON mcp_server TYPE option<array<object>>;
 16→DEFINE FIELD OVERWRITE static_headers[*].name ON mcp_server TYPE string;
 17→DEFINE FIELD OVERWRITE static_headers[*].value_encrypted ON mcp_server TYPE string;
 18→
 19→-- OAuth-specific: linked connected_account for workspace-level OAuth tokens
 20→-- Only populated when auth_mode = "oauth"
 21→DEFINE FIELD OVERWRITE oauth_account ON mcp_server TYPE option<record<connected_account>>;
 22→```
 23→
 24→### `credential_provider` — New Field
 25→
 26→```sql
 27→-- Discovery source: URL of the MCP server that triggered auto-discovery
 28→-- Absent for manually created providers
 29→DEFINE FIELD OVERWRITE discovery_source ON credential_provider TYPE option<string>;
 30→```
 31→
 32→### No Changes Required
 33→
 34→- `connected_account` — existing schema supports OAuth tokens (`access_token_encrypted`, `refresh_token_encrypted`, `token_expires_at`)
 35→- `mcp_tool` — existing `source_server` and `provider` fields are sufficient
 36→
 37→## TypeScript Types
 38→
 39→### Static Headers
 40→
 41→```typescript
 42→type HeaderEntry = {
 43→  name: string;
 44→  value: string;
 45→};
 46→
 47→type EncryptedHeaderEntry = {
 48→  name: string;
 49→  value_encrypted: string;
 50→};
 51→```
 52→
 53→### Auth Mode
 54→
 55→```typescript
 56→type McpServerAuthMode = "none" | "static_headers" | "oauth" | "provider";
 57→
 58→// Extended from existing McpServerListItem
 59→type McpServerRecord = {
 60→  id: string;
 61→  name: string;
 62→  url: string;
 63→  transport: "sse" | "streamable-http";
 64→  workspace: RecordId<"workspace">;
 65→  auth_mode: McpServerAuthMode;
 66→  static_headers?: EncryptedHeaderEntry[];
 67→  oauth_account?: RecordId<"connected_account">;
 68→  provider?: RecordId<"credential_provider">;
 69→  last_status?: string;
 70→  last_error?: string;
 71→  tool_count: number;
 72→  created_at: string;
 73→};
 74→```
 75→
 76→### OAuth Discovery (RFC 9728 + RFC 8414)
 77→
 78→```typescript
 79→// RFC 9728 — Protected Resource Metadata
 80→type ProtectedResourceMetadata = {
 81→  resource: string;
 82→  authorization_servers: string[];
 83→  scopes_supported?: string[];
 84→  bearer_methods_supported?: string[];
